NAME
	away
	away [msg]
	away -clear

DESCRIPTION
	Sets you "away" - when someone tries to tell you something,
	this is what happens (if for example Sumppen used command
	'away in sauna'):

	> tell Sumppen hello?
	Ok, but Sumppen is away: in sauna

SYNTAX
	away
		Shows your current away message, if any.

	away [msg]
		Sets your away message to [msg]

	away -clear
		Removes the away message.

SEE ALSO
	tell
